This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques applied to biomedical event extraction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses recurrent neural networks (RNNs) as the main model, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of entity type embedding, which is a common technique in natural language processing, and could suggest that it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of word embeddings, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, and could suggest that it belongs to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
